    <stitle>AIR CONDITIONING BASIC THEORY, SYSTEM DIAGNOSIS AND SERVICE (with R-134a Refrigerant System) - DESCRIPTION
        OF SYSTEM COMPONENTS - FAN DRIVE AND RADIATOR SHUTTER SOLENOID VALVES
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>FAN DRIVE AND RADIATOR SHUTTER SOLENOID VALVES</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1601922">Figure 21</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1601922" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1601922" filename="../figg16/G1601922.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 21. Typical Solenoid Valve (Fan Drive or Radiator Shutter)</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>The radiator shutters and many fan clutches are operated by compressed air. The air is controlled by
            solenoid valves that are operated by the pressure switches. The valves are all of the same construction, but
            have different operating characteristics depending on the system that they are installed in.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
